# Recaller Project Context

Recaller is a B2B SaaS training execution platform.
Core flow: ingest content → AI generates multi-step plans (2–10 steps, AI-suggested based on content complexity, admin-adjustable) → assign to employees → track completions → notify via Slack/Teams/email → report insights.

## Tech Stack

- Next.js 16 App Router + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS v4
- UI: shadcn/ui (nova preset)
- DB/Auth: Supabase (Postgres + RLS + pgvector)
- AI: Claude 3.7 Sonnet (analysis + reports), GPT-4.1 (plan gen), GPT-4.1 Mini (validation), text-embedding-3-small (1536d)
- Jobs: Inngest | Billing: Stripe | Email: Resend | Observability: Sentry
- Slack: @vercel/slack-bolt + @slack/web-api | Teams: Bot Connector REST API (no BotBuilder SDK)
- Content extraction: youtube-transcript, pdf-parse, mammoth; Whisper only for audio/video without transcripts

## Build Order (strict)

Phase 0 accounts → 1 schema/auth → 2 content ingestion → 3 AI plans → 4 employee UI → 5 manager dashboard → 6 Slack bot → 7 Teams bot → 8 notifications/nudges → 9 billing → 10 insights → 11 calendar → 12 deploy

## Key Architecture Decisions

- Tenant boundary is `org_id` everywhere (DB, API, notifications)
- NotificationService routes to Slack/Teams/email based on org+user identity fields
- Runtime analytics uses pre-written SQL; AI only writes narrative (never generates production SQL)
- All routes under `src/app/dashboard/` for admin, `src/app/employee/` for employees
- Supabase SSR pattern: browser client, server client with cookies, middleware for session refresh + route protection

